# =============================================================================
# cluster.cfg — Site-specific configuration for qchem-spectra workflow
# =============================================================================
# Copy this file to cluster.cfg and fill in the values for your cluster.
# cluster.cfg is sourced automatically by each script at startup; CLI flags
# always override values set here.
#
# Supported variables (all optional):
#   QCHEM_SETUP             — path to the Q-Chem setup script (sets QC, QCAUX, PATH)
#   CLUSTER_PARTITION       — default SLURM partition name
#   CLUSTER_WALL            — default SLURM wall-clock limit (HH:MM:SS)
#                             Note: each script has its own stage-appropriate default;
#                             set this only if you want a global override.
#   CLUSTER_LD_LIBRARY_PATH — colon-separated list of extra library directories
#                             prepended to LD_LIBRARY_PATH in each SLURM job.
#                             Required when the Q-Chem installation depends on
#                             libraries not present in the compute node's default
#                             environment. What you need here depends on how
#                             Q-Chem was compiled:
#
#                             Intel-compiled Q-Chem (most common):
#                               Needs libiomp5.so (Intel OpenMP runtime) and a
#                               libstdc++.so.6 new enough to match the GCC used
#                               during compilation. Add both the Intel compiler
#                               lib dir and a sufficiently new GCC lib64 dir.
#                               Example:
#                                 CLUSTER_LD_LIBRARY_PATH=\
#                                   /path/to/intel/compiler/lib:\
#                                   /path/to/gcc-X.Y.Z/lib64
#
#                             GCC-compiled Q-Chem:
#                               Only needs a compatible libstdc++.so.6 if the
#                               compute nodes run an older OS than the build host.
#                               Example:
#                                 CLUSTER_LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/path/to/gcc-X.Y.Z/lib64
#
#                             Leave unset if the compute nodes already have all
#                             required libraries in their default environment.
# =============================================================================

# Full path to the Q-Chem setup script for your installation
QCHEM_SETUP=/path/to/qchem/setqc

# SLURM defaults
CLUSTER_PARTITION=general
# CLUSTER_WALL=04:00:00    # uncomment to override per-script defaults

# Extra library paths needed by the Q-Chem executable (see notes above)
# CLUSTER_LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/path/to/intel/compiler/lib:/path/to/gcc-X.Y.Z/lib64
